* DONE ask for confirmation if there is active alarm and user want to close
  browser window. prevent accident close.

  how to do this in JS?

  I know dropbox will show a message if uploading is not finished and you try
  to close the window. how they do it?

  ref: http://www.openjs.com/scripts/events/exit_confirmation.php

  in beforeunload event handler, if you set event.returnValue to a string,
  firefox will display a confirm window showing that message.

  https://developer.mozilla.org/en/DOM/window.onbeforeunload
  this page does say what to do, but it doesn't say setting that value will
  display a dialog and prevent window from closing.
